      "writtenOn": "2020-09-18T04:09:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is this persistent in a user session (i.e. unless the user close the browser, the setting will be there)? Then theoretically we can have a very long user session, so let\u0027s say if we update to V3, do we need to worry about migrating both v2 -\u003e v3 and v1 -\u003e v3?\n\nI don\u0027t expect that we will have a lot of backward incompatible changes:\n1. Adding a new key: the old settings does not have this key, so we should use the default value\n2. Deleting a key: We can just ignore the key for the old settings\n3. Change the meaning of a key: I expect that we should not do this.\n\nSo I wonder whether it worths it to introduce versioning here.",
